{{!--
  ============================================================================
  SERVICE INSTRUCTIONS - ENGLAND SECTION 8 / FORM 3A
  ============================================================================
  Stage-aware support document for the current England Form 3A notice workflow.
--}}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Service Instructions - {{notice_name}}</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 10mm;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      color: #1f1635;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .hero,
    .summary-box,
    .step-card,
    .risk-box,
    .note-box {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .hero {
      border: 1px solid #ddd6fe;
      background: #faf8ff;
      padding: 1.2em;
      margin-bottom: 1.1em;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      margin: 0 0 0.2em 0;
      font-size: 18pt;
    }

    .hero h2 {
      margin: 0 0 0.35em 0;
      font-size: 11pt;
      color: #5b5370;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }

    .hero p {
      margin: 0.25em 0;
    }

    .summary-box,
    .step-card,
    .note-box {
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 1em;
      margin-bottom: 0.9em;
    }

    .summary-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
      gap: 0.45em 0.9em;
    }

    .summary-grid dt {
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #5b5370;
    }

    .summary-grid dd {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .section-title {
      margin: 1.25em 0 0.65em 0;
      font-size: 12pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #231942;
    }

    .steps-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.9em;
    }

    .step-number {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.45em;
      padding: 0.18em 0.55em;
      border-radius: 0;
      background: #ede9fe;
      color: #4c1d95;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .step-card h3,
    .note-box h3,
    .risk-box h3 {
      margin: 0 0 0.45em 0;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      color: #231942;
    }

    .step-card p,
    .note-box p,
    .risk-box p {
      margin: 0.3em 0;
    }

    .step-card ul,
    .note-box ul {
      margin: 0.4em 0 0 1.1em;
    }

    .step-card li,
    .note-box li {
      margin: 0.25em 0;
    }

    .risk-box {
      border: 1px solid #fecaca;
      background: #fef2f2;
      padding: 1em;
      margin-top: 1em;
    }

    .risk-chip {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.45em;
      padding: 0.18em 0.55em;
      border-radius: 0;
      background: #fee2e2;
      color: #991b1b;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .muted {
      color: #6b7280;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="hero">
    <h2>{{pack_title}}</h2>
    <h1>Service Playbook</h1>
    <p><strong>{{notice_name}}</strong> is the current Form 3A Section 8 notice for England.</p>
    <p>{{pack_supporting_line}}</p>
    <p class="muted">{{risk_line}}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="summary-box">
    <dl class="summary-grid">
      <dt>Property</dt>
      <dd>{{property_address}}</dd>
      <dt>Tenant</dt>
      <dd>{{tenant_full_name}}{{#if tenant_2_name}}, {{tenant_2_name}}{{/if}}</dd>
      <dt>Notice</dt>
      <dd>{{notice_name}}</dd>
      {{#if (hasValue service_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Notice service date</dt>
      <dd>{{service_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue notice_expiry_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Notice expiry date</dt>
      <dd>{{notice_expiry_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue earliest_proceedings_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Earliest proceedings date</dt>
      <dd>{{earliest_proceedings_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue latest_proceedings_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Latest proceedings date</dt>
      <dd>{{latest_proceedings_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
    </dl>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">Service Playbook</h2>
  <div class="steps-grid">
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-number">Step 1 — Prepare</div>
      <h3>Prepare the notice pack before anything is served</h3>
      <p>Print or save the {{notice_name}}, keep a clean copy, and make sure the notice date, expiry date, and earliest proceedings date all match the rest of the file.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep one clean copy for service and one copy for your records.</li>
        <li>Check that the grounds, dates, and arrears schedule line up before the notice leaves your hands.</li>
        <li>Keep the compliance snapshot with the file so you know what still needs attention.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-number">Step 2 — Serve</div>
      <h3>Serve the Form 3A notice in a way you can prove later</h3>
      {{#if (eq service_method "post")}}
      <p>Use first class post and keep the proof of posting. This is usually the cleanest option when you need a straightforward service record.</p>
      {{else if (eq service_method "recorded_delivery")}}
      <p>Recorded or signed delivery can help with tracking, but be careful if the item is refused or not collected because that can create avoidable disputes.</p>
      {{else if (eq service_method "hand")}}
      <p>Hand delivery can work well when you can record the date, location, and how the notice was left or handed over.</p>
      {{else}}
      <p>Use the service method recorded in the pack and make sure it matches the tenancy file and the N215 record.</p>
      {{/if}}
      <ul>
        <li>Serve the same notice that appears in this pack.</li>
        <li>Record the exact date of service and the method used.</li>
        <li>Do not alter the service record after the event unless you are correcting it transparently across the whole file.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-number">Step 3 — Record</div>
      <h3>Build the service evidence immediately</h3>
      <p>Keep proof of posting, delivery notes, photographs, or attendance notes straight away. Service evidence is often what saves or weakens the case later.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep proof of posting or a written attendance note.</li>
        <li>Keep the served notice copy with the same dates shown on the N215 certificate.</li>
        <li>Store every service document in the same case file so nothing has to be rebuilt later.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-number">Step 4 — Align</div>
      <h3>Keep the notice, N215, and later court file saying the same thing</h3>
      <p>Most possession cases fail on inconsistency, not because the landlord lacked a form. Keep the notice, service record, arrears evidence, and any later court paperwork aligned from the start.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Check the notice date, expiry date, and earliest proceedings date against the whole file.</li>
        <li>Make sure the grounds and arrears position stay consistent if the case moves into court.</li>
        {{#if (eq pack_stage "stage2")}}
        <li>Carry the same facts into Form N5, Form N119, the witness statement, and the hearing bundle.</li>
        {{else}}
        <li>If the tenant does not leave, move into Stage 2 so the court file builds directly from this served notice record.</li>
        {{/if}}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="risk-box">
    <div class="risk-chip">Failure risk</div>
    <h3>Incorrect service can delay or undermine the claim</h3>
    <p>If the tenant disputes service or the dates do not match across the notice, N215, and later court papers, the case can be delayed or weakened even where the underlying grounds are sound.</p>
    <p><strong>Action:</strong> Keep the service record complete and aligned before you move on.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">File Notes</h2>
  <div class="note-box">
    {{#if drafting_model.serviceInstructions.overviewParagraphs.length}}
      {{#each drafting_model.serviceInstructions.overviewParagraphs}}
      <p>{{this}}</p>
      {{/each}}
    {{else}}
      <p>This guidance is practical support only. Check the tenancy agreement, your evidence file, and current official guidance before serving the notice.</p>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
</body>
</html>
